        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:28PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Crossroads Village to near Cohoctah.
Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Flint, Fenton, Lapeer, Flushing, Grand Blanc, Davison, Clio,
Columbiaville, Burton, Swartz Creek, Hadley, Linden, Mount Morris,
Goodrich, Otisville, Metamora, Otter Lake, Beecher, Crossroads
Village, and Lake Fenton.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
